* Promoting and demoting headings::
@end menu

@node Promoting and demoting headings
@section Promoting and demoting headings

@findex outline-extras-promote-heading
@findex outline-extras-demote-heading
When restructuring a document you often need to promote or demote a heading together with its subtree. The built-in commands @code{outline-promote} and @code{outline-demote} accept a prefix argument of @code{C-u} to operate on the entire subtree, but after the operation point may land on the line below the heading rather than on the heading itself. This is disorienting when you want to perform several adjustments in sequence.

The command @code{outline-extras-promote-heading} promotes the current heading and its subtree by one level, then moves point back to the heading line. Similarly, @code{outline-extras-demote-heading} demotes the heading and its subtree by one level and repositions point on the heading. Both commands achieve this by calling the underlying @samp{outline-promote} or @samp{outline-demote} with a prefix argument of 4 and then invoking @code{outline-previous-heading} to correct the cursor position.

These commands are most useful when bound to convenient keys so that you can rapidly restructure an outline without losing your place.

